<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="middle-n">middle <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'mɪdl/    美 /'mɪdl/  </p>
<p>[常作the middle]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>中间；中央：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That dress has a dirty spot right <strong>in the middle</strong>. 
那件衣服的正中间有个污点。</p><footer>人教 – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Switzerland is a small but beautiful country <strong>in the middle of</strong> Europe.
瑞士位于欧洲中部，很小却很美。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(时间的) 中点；(事件的) 中途</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>in the middle of (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In many parts of the world, people take naps in the middle of the day.
在世界上许多地方，人们中午会小睡一会儿。</p><footer>2008 四川</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was in the middle of packing up my things when suddenly the power went out in the neighborhood.
我正在收拾东西，突然整个街区都停电了。</p></div></div>